VL  - 4
IS  - 3
SP  - 253
EP  - 262
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/08/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(76)90036-1
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407676900361
AB  - Using two sets of U.S. railroad data with two outputs and three inputs, we estimated production function parameters via the system of derived input demand functions, and via the dual cost function. The results indicate increasing returns to scale, and a violation of required convexity for the production function.
